Citigroup Incurred Losses on 21% of Trading Days Last Year, Filing Shows

-- B y   D o n a l   G r i f f i n
-- 
2011-02-25T22:51:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/citigroup-incurred-losses-on-21-of-trading-days-last-year-filing-shows.html
  Citigroup Inc ., the third-largest  U.S. bank  by assets, said it had trading losses on 21 percent of
the days when markets were open in 2010.  Losses occurred on 55 of 260 trading days last year,
compared with the 58 days reported for 2009, according to a
regulatory filing by the New York-based firm today. The losses
surpassed $100 million on one day last year, the filing shows.
They had exceeded $400 million on two days a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
